snippet.textDisplay:
I know its not really "fun" for them, but honestly I think the safest way to have small dogs in the car is in individual, hard kennels. You can fill them with blankets for comfort and strap the kennel in sideways, so ideally, your dog is laying down and if something does happen, they just roll lengthwise into the side of the kennel and take very minimal damage, if any, and broken glass will hit the kennel shell instead of your dog.

The real struggle is finding a safe way to transport big dogs lol. We have some of those seat belt harness things, which is better than nothing, but they dont seem effective enough to me. Even if they did make these carseats for bigger dogs though, I dont think I like the idea. Seems like it would be bad for their back/hips in the long run. Maybe if they were designed to strap them in sideways, so they could lay down comfortably while held tightly in. That way the weight of the impact in an accident would be more evenly distributed along the length of their body, instead of across their chest, and in general, their own body weight would be held naturally, so they wouldnt have unnecessary stress on their back or joints.

I didnt mean to say that much, guess the thought train just took off 😅
